This is the Upstream changelog. New features / fixes are marked with (+), and known issues are marked with (-).

Upstream 0.2.0 (Marlowe) - 3rd December 2006
---------------------------------------------
+ Upstream-base now has a dialog based wizard interface, as well as the quick --flag option.
+ Modules are now checked against a list of known md5sums, to avoid hijacking.
- Not all md5 sums are entered, nor is the user warned when an unvalidated module is used
+ More log-modules and submit-modules added.

Upstream 0.1.0 (Chaucer) - 6th November 2006
---------------------------------------------
-Canoe and Kayak have no error catching, input validation. Kayak crashes if a form field is left empty.
